<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-2493] Rename lucene/solr dev jar files to -SNAPSHOT.jar</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2493</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently the lucene dev jar files end with &apos;-dev.jar&apos; this is all fine, but it makes people using maven jump through a few hoops to get the -SNAPSHOT naming convention required by maven.  If we want to publish snapshot builds with hudson, we would need to either write some crazy scripts or run the build twice.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I suggest we switch to -SNAPSHOT.jar.  Hopefully for the 3.x branch and for the /trunk (4.x) branch&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
